# Backlog management

Canonical backlog: [docs/backlog.md](../../docs/backlog.md).

## Always

- Treat the backlog as an **ordered table** — column **Order** (integer, lower = higher priority).
- When adding, removing, promoting, completing, or deprioritizing ideas, **update the table** and **renumber Order** so active (`idea` / `ready`) ranks stay contiguous starting at 1.
- Prefer **reordering** over long prose lists; keep one row per idea.

## When to update

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| User asks for ideas / backlog / prioritization | Propose rows; write them into `docs/backlog.md` if accepted |
| New product idea in chat (not starting analysis yet) | Add `idea` row; assign Order |
| Starting feature analysis for a backlog idea | Status → `promoted`; link `feature/<slug>.md` |
| Feature changelog marked `done` | Matching backlog row → `done` (or remove from active ranks and renumber) |
| User rejects an idea | Status → `wont`; renumber remaining |
| User says “prioritize X” / “move Y up” | Reorder **Order** values; do not invent silent priority changes |

## Do not

- Put implementation tasks (T1, T2…) in the backlog — those live in `feature/*.md`.
- Duplicate the full feature analysis in the backlog — one-line **Why / notes** + slug + link.
- Start phase 5 coding from a backlog row alone — still follow [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc).

## Relation to feature docs

```
backlog idea → feature analysis (feature/<slug>.md) → … → done
     ↑                      ↓
  Order / Status      Status: promoted + Feature doc link
```

Promoted work may keep a backlog row for visibility until `done`.
